  { question: "Should I use UUID or auto-increment IDs in my database?", answer: "Auto-increment IDs are simpler and more compact but expose record counts and are hard to use across distributed systems. UUIDs work across multiple databases and services without coordination, but are larger (16 bytes vs 4-8 bytes) and can hurt index performance. UUID v7 (time-ordered) is a good middle ground." },
